22/01/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy met with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer on Wednesday (21 January), discussing co-operation between the OSCE and NATO.
Bulgaria assumed the OSCE Chairmanship-in-Office on 1 January.
Passy said successful co-operation related to the Balkans could be extended to other regions, including Afghanistan.
In other news Wednesday, the Bulgarian Parliament ratified the free trade agreement with Bosnia and Herzegovina.
It is aimed at boosting bilateral trade and business relations.
(Trud, Dnevnik - 22/01/04;
BTA, BNT, BNR - 21/01/04)
